ase that the system would shut down in the middle of a work session! \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 104 "In t
he text mode (click on the cap T button) place your name(s) and date a
t the top of your worksheet.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "1.  Graph
ing functions and the " }{TEXT 257 4 "plot" }{TEXT -1 89 " command.  T
he Maple command for plotting the graph of an explicitly defined funct
ion is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 
"     " }{TEXT 258 0 "" }{TEXT 259 4 "plot" }{TEXT 260 0 "" }{TEXT -1 
2 "( " }{TEXT 261 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 266 1 "x" }{TEXT 
-1 20 "=range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 262 4 "expr" }{TEXT 267 1 " " }
{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 264 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "
which represents the function to be plotted and " }{TEXT 263 1 "x" }
{TEXT -1 38 " is the independent variable used in  " }{TEXT 265 4 "exp
r" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 81 "Several options exist to change
 way the plot will appear.  These options include:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 126 "            y=range     \+
                  this allows the user to specifiy the range of output
 values which Maple will display" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "    \+
        thickness=value           this controls the thickness of the p
lotted curve.  value = 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
119 "            color=value                 this sets the color of th
e plotted curve.  value = red, green, blue, cyan, etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 160 "For each of the fol
lowing functions provide a plot to represent the graph the function.  \+
Choose a range that will optimally represent the features of the graph
." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "a.  \+
  y = 3x - 1" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "f1:=3*x-1;" 
